genresAdvancedInfo.name: french folk
genresAdvancedInfo.description: French folk is a genre that celebrates the traditional music of France. It features acoustic instruments such as the accordion, fiddle, and guitar, and often includes vocals sung in French. The lyrics often tell stories of rural life, love, and nature, and the melodies are simple and catchy.
